chat-names

From IndieWeb
Jump to: navigation, search

Chat names is a list of chat regulars sorted by nickname, with their website and usual timezone(s).

Note: the name of a city does not imply that someone lives there. It's from the list of timezone names. E.g. US 48-state folks can typically just use:

  • "America/Los_Angeles" (Pacific), "America/Denver" (Mountain), "America/Chicago" (Central), "America/New_York" (Eastern)

Contents

  • 1 Nicknames
  • 2 Timezone Aliases
  • 3 FAQ
    • 3.1 Why is my image not in the logs
  • 4 See Also

Nicknames

Please keep sorted alphabetically. Please only add yourself, your URL, and your icon, using the Template:chat-user template.

Part of the point of this page is to have individuals themselves edit this page and add their URL and icon as they intend it to show up in chat logs. If you see someone on chat who lacks a URL or icon, encourage them, per welcoming.

Timezone Aliases

Through usage, it's apparent that having aliases for IANA Time Zone names would help with being more permissive with what people enter for themselves. Here's a list of alias/actual names of time zones:

America/San_Francisco
America/Los_Angeles

FAQ

Why is my image not in the logs

Q: I added my image to the above list of chat names, and it shows up there, so why isn't it showing up in the logs?

A: Wait five minutes and reload.
